  30:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****       The CORDIC HAL driver can be used as follows:
ARM GAS  /tmp/ccfE7y8y.s 			page 2


  31:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c **** 
  32:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****       (#) Initialize the CORDIC low level resources by implementing the HAL_CORDIC_MspInit():
  33:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****          (++) Enable the CORDIC interface clock using __HAL_RCC_CORDIC_CLK_ENABLE()
  34:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****          (++) In case of using interrupts (e.g. HAL_CORDIC_Calculate_IT())
  35:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****              (+++) Configure the CORDIC interrupt priority using HAL_NVIC_SetPriority()
  36:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****              (+++) Enable the CORDIC IRQ handler using HAL_NVIC_EnableIRQ()
  37:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****              (+++) In CORDIC IRQ handler, call HAL_CORDIC_IRQHandler()
  38:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****          (++) In case of using DMA to control data transfer (e.g. HAL_CORDIC_Calculate_DMA())
  39:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****              (+++) Enable the DMA2 interface clock using
  40:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****                  __HAL_RCC_DMA2_CLK_ENABLE()
  41:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****              (+++) Configure and enable two DMA channels one for managing data transfer from
  42:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****                  memory to peripheral (input channel) and another channel for managing data
  43:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****                  transfer from peripheral to memory (output channel)
  44:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****              (+++) Associate the initialized DMA handle to the CORDIC DMA handle
  45:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****                  using __HAL_LINKDMA()
  46:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****              (+++) Configure the priority and enable the NVIC for the transfer complete
  47:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****                  interrupt on the two DMA channels.
  48:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****                  Resort to HAL_NVIC_SetPriority() and HAL_NVIC_EnableIRQ()
  49:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c **** 
  50:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****       (#) Initialize the CORDIC HAL using HAL_CORDIC_Init(). This function
  51:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****          (++) resorts to HAL_CORDIC_MspInit() for low-level initialization,
  52:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c **** 
  53:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****       (#) Configure CORDIC processing (calculation) using HAL_CORDIC_Configure().
  54:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****           This function configures:
  55:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****          (++) Processing functions: Cosine, Sine, Phase, Modulus, Arctangent,
  56:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****               Hyperbolic cosine, Hyperbolic sine, Hyperbolic arctangent,
  57:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****               Natural log, Square root
  58:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****          (++) Scaling factor: 1 to 2exp(-7)
  59:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****          (++) Width of input data: 32 bits input data size (Q1.31 format) or 16 bits
  60:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****               input data size (Q1.15 format)
  61:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****          (++) Width of output data: 32 bits output data size (Q1.31 format) or 16 bits
  62:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****               output data size (Q1.15 format)
  63:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****          (++) Number of 32-bit write expected for one calculation: One 32-bits write
  64:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****               or Two 32-bit write
  65:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****          (++) Number of 32-bit read expected after one calculation: One 32-bits read
  66:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****               or Two 32-bit read
  67:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****          (++) Precision: 1 to 15 cycles for calculation (the more cycles, the better precision)
  68:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c **** 
  69:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****       (#) Four processing (calculation) functions are available:
  70:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****          (++) Polling mode: processing API is blocking function
  71:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****               i.e. it processes the data and wait till the processing is finished
  72:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****               API is HAL_CORDIC_Calculate
  73:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****          (++) Polling Zero-overhead mode: processing API is blocking function
  74:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****               i.e. it processes the data and wait till the processing is finished
  75:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****               A bit faster than standard polling mode, but blocking also AHB bus
  76:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****               API is HAL_CORDIC_CalculateZO
  77:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****          (++) Interrupt mode: processing API is not blocking functions
  78:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****               i.e. it processes the data under interrupt
  79:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****               API is HAL_CORDIC_Calculate_IT
  80:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****          (++) DMA mode: processing API is not blocking functions and the CPU is
  81:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****               not used for data transfer,
  82:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****               i.e. the data transfer is ensured by DMA
  83:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****               API is HAL_CORDIC_Calculate_DMA
  84:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c **** 
  85:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****       (#) Call HAL_CORDIC_DeInit() to de-initialize the CORDIC peripheral. This function
  86:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****          (++) resorts to HAL_CORDIC_MspDeInit() for low-level de-initialization,
  87:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c **** 
ARM GAS  /tmp/ccfE7y8y.s 			page 3


  88:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****   *** Callback registration ***
  89:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****   =============================================
  90:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c **** 
  91:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****   The compilation define  USE_HAL_CORDIC_REGISTER_CALLBACKS when set to 1
  92:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****   allows the user to configure dynamically the driver callbacks.
  93:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****   Use Function HAL_CORDIC_RegisterCallback() to register an interrupt callback.
  94:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c **** 
  95:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****   Function HAL_CORDIC_RegisterCallback() allows to register following callbacks:
  96:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****     (+) ErrorCallback             : Error Callback.
  97:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****     (+) CalculateCpltCallback     : Calculate complete Callback.
  98:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****     (+) MspInitCallback           : CORDIC MspInit.
  99:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****     (+) MspDeInitCallback         : CORDIC MspDeInit.
 100:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****   This function takes as parameters the HAL peripheral handle, the Callback ID
 101:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****   and a pointer to the user callback function.
 102:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c **** 
 103:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****   Use function HAL_CORDIC_UnRegisterCallback() to reset a callback to the default
 104:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****   weak function.
 105:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****   HAL_CORDIC_UnRegisterCallback takes as parameters the HAL peripheral handle,
 106:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****   and the Callback ID.
 107:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****   This function allows to reset following callbacks:
 108:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****     (+) ErrorCallback             : Error Callback.
 109:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****     (+) CalculateCpltCallback     : Calculate complete Callback.
 110:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****     (+) MspInitCallback           : CORDIC MspInit.
 111:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****     (+) MspDeInitCallback         : CORDIC MspDeInit.
 112:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c **** 
 113:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****   By default, after the HAL_CORDIC_Init() and when the state is HAL_CORDIC_STATE_RESET,
 114:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****   all callbacks are set to the corresponding weak functions:
 115:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****   examples HAL_CORDIC_ErrorCallback(), HAL_CORDIC_CalculateCpltCallback().
 116:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****   Exception done for MspInit and MspDeInit functions that are
 117:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****   reset to the legacy weak function in the HAL_CORDIC_Init()/ HAL_CORDIC_DeInit() only when
 118:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****   these callbacks are null (not registered beforehand).
 119:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****   if not, MspInit or MspDeInit are not null, the HAL_CORDIC_Init()/ HAL_CORDIC_DeInit()
 120:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****   keep and use the user MspInit/MspDeInit callbacks (registered beforehand)
 121:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c **** 
 122:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****   Callbacks can be registered/unregistered in HAL_CORDIC_STATE_READY state only.
 123:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****   Exception done MspInit/MspDeInit that can be registered/unregistered
 124:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****   in HAL_CORDIC_STATE_READY or HAL_CORDIC_STATE_RESET state,
 125:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****   thus registered (user) MspInit/DeInit callbacks can be used during the Init/DeInit.
 126:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****   In that case first register the MspInit/MspDeInit user callbacks
 127:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****   using HAL_CORDIC_RegisterCallback() before calling HAL_CORDIC_DeInit()
 128:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****   or HAL_CORDIC_Init() function.
 129:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c **** 
 130:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****   When The compilation define USE_HAL_CORDIC_REGISTER_CALLBACKS is set to 0 or
 131:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****   not defined, the callback registration feature is not available and all callbacks
 132:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****   are set to the corresponding weak functions.
 133:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c **** 
 134:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****   @endverbatim
 135:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****   ******************************************************************************
 136:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_cordic.c ****   */
